# Ways of Working: {{ display_name }}

## Definition of Done

A feature is **done** when all of the following are true:

- [ ] Code passes `pnpm lint` and `pnpm type-check` with zero errors
- [ ] All new components have explicit `loading` and `error` states
- [ ] Tests are written per the **{{ test_strategy }}** strategy (see below)
- [ ] Lighthouse CI score does not regress (Performance >= 85, Accessibility = 100, Best Practices >= 90)
- [ ] Core Web Vitals targets are met on the preview URL (LCP < 2.5 s, CLS < 0.1, INP < 200 ms)
- [ ] No accessibility violations at WCAG 2.1 AA level (`axe` or `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y`)
- [ ] Code has been reviewed and approved by at least one team member
- [ ] The feature works at 320 px, 768 px, and 1280 px viewport widths
- [ ] Documentation is updated if the change affects architecture or conventions
{% if use_storybook %}
- [ ] New UI components have a Storybook story covering the default and key variant states
{% endif %}

