## Component Naming Conventions

### Files

| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Component file | PascalCase | `UserCard.tsx` |
| Component directory | PascalCase | `UserCard/index.tsx` |
| Hook file | camelCase prefixed `use` | `useUserData.ts` |
| Utility file | camelCase | `formatDate.ts` |
| Type file | camelCase | `user.types.ts` |
| Service file | camelCase | `users.service.ts` |
| Style file (module) | matches component | `UserCard.module.css` |
| Story file | matches component | `UserCard.stories.tsx` |
| Test file | matches component | `UserCard.test.tsx` |

### Component exports

Every component file exports the component as a **named export**. Default exports are only used by Next.js page and layout files.

```tsx
// Good
export function UserCard({ user }: UserCardProps) { ... }

// Avoid (except for pages/layouts)
export default function UserCard() { ... }
```

### Barrel exports

Each `src/components/ui/`, `src/components/layout/`, and `src/components/features/` directory has an `index.ts` that re-exports its public API.

```ts
// src/components/ui/index.ts
export { Button, type ButtonProps } from "./Button";
export { Input, type InputProps } from "./Input";
export { Badge } from "./Badge";
```

Import from the barrel, not the file directly:

```ts
// Good
import { Button, Input } from "@/components/ui";

// Avoid
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/Button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/Input";
```

