## Branching Strategy

Trunk-based development with short-lived feature branches.

### Branch Names

```
feature/<ticket-id>-short-description
fix/<ticket-id>-short-description
chore/description
docs/description
```

### Workflow

1. Create branch from `main`
2. Make small, focused commits (aim for < 400 LOC per PR)
3. Open a Draft PR early to get CI feedback
4. Mark ready for review when complete
5. Squash-merge into `main`
6. Delete the branch after merge

---

## Pull Request Conventions

### PR Title

Follow Conventional Commits format:

```
feat(users): add avatar upload to profile page
fix(auth): resolve session expiry redirect loop
perf(dashboard): lazy-load chart components
a11y(nav): improve keyboard navigation in sidebar
chore(deps): upgrade Next.js to 15.2
```

**Scope** should be a feature area or route (`users`, `auth`, `dashboard`, `settings`, `ui`).

### PR Description

```markdown
## What
Brief summary of the change.

## Why
Ticket link or motivation.

## How
Implementation approach (if non-obvious).

## Screenshots / Video
(for UI changes)

## Checklist
- [ ] Lint passes
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Lighthouse score checked
- [ ] Responsive layout verified
```

### Review Expectations

- Review within 1 business day
- Approve if the implementation is correct and follows conventions, even if you'd do it differently
- Block only for correctness issues, security problems, or convention violations
- Resolve your own comments once addressed; don't wait for the author to dismiss

