## Accessibility Requirements

This project targets **WCAG 2.1 Level AA** compliance.

### Mandatory

- All interactive elements are keyboard-operable (Tab, Enter, Space, Escape, Arrow keys)
- All images have descriptive `alt` text (or `alt=""` for decorative images)
- Form inputs have associated `<label>` elements (or `aria-label`)
- Focus is always visible (`outline` must not be `none` without a styled replacement)
- Colour contrast ratio >= 4.5:1 for normal text, >= 3:1 for large text
- No content relies on colour alone to convey meaning
- Modals trap focus and return focus to the trigger on close
- Live regions (`aria-live`) announce dynamic content changes to screen readers

### Tooling

- `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y` runs in CI - zero warnings allowed
- Run `axe` in browser DevTools before marking a PR ready for review
- Screen-reader test (VoiceOver / NVDA) for complex interactive patterns

