## Testing Expectations

Strategy: **{{ test_strategy }}**

{% if test_strategy == "vitest-only" %}
### Vitest (Unit + Component Tests)

- Every custom hook (`src/hooks/`) has a test file
- Every utility function (`src/lib/`) has a test file
- Feature components with non-trivial logic have a component test using `@testing-library/react`
- Component tests use `render`, `screen`, `userEvent` - never query by test ID unless absolutely necessary
- Mock only at the network boundary (use `msw` for API mocks, not `vi.mock` on service functions)
- Target: >= 80 % branch coverage on `src/lib/` and `src/hooks/`

**Test naming:**

```ts
describe("UserCard", () => {
  it("renders the user display name", () => { ... });
  it("shows a fallback avatar when imageUrl is null", () => { ... });
  it("calls onDelete when the delete button is clicked", async () => { ... });
});
```

{% elif test_strategy == "vitest-and-playwright" %}
### Vitest (Unit + Component Tests)

- All hooks and utilities have Vitest unit tests
- Feature components have component tests with `@testing-library/react`
- Use `msw` for network mocking in tests
- Target: >= 80% branch coverage on `src/lib/` and `src/hooks/`

### Playwright (End-to-End)

- Every critical user journey has a Playwright test
- Tests run against a local `next dev` or `next start` server
- Use Page Object Models for reusable interactions
- Prefer `getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByText` over test IDs
- Tests must pass in Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit

**Key journeys to cover:**
{% if use_auth %}
- Authentication: login, logout, token expiry redirect
{% endif %}
- Primary happy path for the main feature
- Form validation (valid submit, invalid fields)
- Error states (API failure, 404)

{% elif test_strategy == "jest-and-cypress" %}
### Jest (Unit + Component Tests)

- All hooks and utilities have Jest unit tests
- Feature components have component tests with `@testing-library/react`
- Use `msw` for network mocking
- Target: >= 80% branch coverage on `src/lib/` and `src/hooks/`

### Cypress (End-to-End)

- Every critical user journey has a Cypress test
- Use `cy.intercept()` to stub slow or flaky API calls
- Prefer `cy.findByRole()` (Testing Library Cypress) over `.get('[data-testid]')`

{% endif %}

