## Storybook Requirements

- Every component in `src/components/ui/` **must** have a story
- Feature components with multiple visual states should have stories
- Each story must render correctly in isolation (no context dependencies without decorators)
- Stories must cover: default state, all key variants, loading state, error/empty state
- Use `@storybook/test` (play functions) for interaction tests on complex components

**Story naming:**

```ts
// UserCard.stories.tsx
export default {
  title: "Features/UserCard",
  component: UserCard,
} satisfies Meta<typeof UserCard>;

export const Default: Story = { args: { user: mockUser } };
export const WithoutAvatar: Story = { args: { user: { ...mockUser, imageUrl: null } } };
export const Loading: Story = { ... };
```

{% endif %}

