## AI Collaboration Guidelines

{% if ai_context %}
This project is optimised for AI-assisted development.

### For AI Agents

- Read `AI_CONTEXT.md` before starting any task
- Follow the patterns in `docs/architecture.md` exactly
- Use `docs/page-templates/` as the structural reference for new pages
- Write tests matching the **{{ test_strategy }}** strategy
- Write an ADR if introducing a new library or pattern
- Never add `"use client"` without justification

### For Developers Working with AI

- Give the agent a clear, scoped task with file-level context
- Reference specific docs and patterns in your prompt
- Review AI output against the same DoD and PR standards as human code
- Update `AI_CONTEXT.md` when patterns change so the agent stays aligned
{% else %}
When using AI coding assistants:

- Provide project context: share `docs/architecture.md` with the agent
- Scope tasks clearly - one feature or component at a time
- Review generated code against DoD and coding conventions
- Ensure tests are included - do not accept code without tests
{% endif %}
